@EndNode


@Node MP3File "GUI / MP3 file"

@{_Section "MP3 file"}

  This text gadget only displays the MPEG Audio filename, without the path.

@EndNode

@Node MP3Duration "GUI / MP3 duration"

@{_Section "MP3 duration"}

  This text gadget only displays the duration of the MPEG Audio file.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU}  Every MPEG Audio file is supported so  the  duration  calculation
  should always be performed. Tell @{" me " link AUTHOR} if it's not the case.

@EndNode

@Node MP3Title "GUI / MP3 title"

@{_Section "MP3 title"}

  This string gadget allows you to view/change the TAG ID3 title.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU} If you alter the contents of this gadget and press RETURN,  then  a
  requester  will prompt you to write the TAG ID3 in case you press « @{U}Okay@{UU} »
  or « @{U}Cancel@{UU} ».

@EndNode

@Node MP3Artist "GUI / MP3 artist"

@{_Section "MP3 artist"}

  This string gadget allows you to view/change the TAG ID3 artist.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU} If you alter the contents of this gadget and press RETURN,  then  a
  requester  will prompt you to write the TAG ID3 in case you press « @{U}Okay@{UU} »
  or « @{U}Cancel@{UU} ».

@EndNode

@Node MP3Album "GUI / MP3 album"

@{_Section "MP3 album"}

  This string gadget allows you to view/change the TAG ID3 album.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU} If you alter the contents of this gadget and press RETURN,  then  a
  requester  will prompt you to write the TAG ID3 in case you press « @{U}Okay@{UU} »
  or « @{U}Cancel@{UU} ».

@EndNode

@Node MP3Comment "GUI / MP3 comment"

@{_Section "MP3 comment"}

  This string gadget allows you to view/change the TAG ID3 comment.

  If the @{" TN=TRACKNUMBER/S " link TRACKNUMBER} option is specified on command line, the comment
  field is limited to 28 chars because of the two bytes taken from the Track
  field. More info about it @{" here " link TAGID3}.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU} If you alter the contents of this gadget and press RETURN,  then  a
  requester  will prompt you to write the TAG ID3 in case you press « @{U}Okay@{UU} »
  or « @{U}Cancel@{UU} ».

@EndNode

@Node MP3Year "GUI / MP3 year"

@{_Section "MP3 year"}

  This string gadget allows you to view/change the TAG ID3 year.

@EndNode

@Node MP3GenreText "GUI / MP3 genre text"

@{_Section "MP3 genre text"}

  This text gadget allows you to view the TAG ID3 genre.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU} If you alter the contents of this gadget and press RETURN,  then  a
  requester  will prompt you to write the TAG ID3 in case you press « @{U}Okay@{UU} »
  or « @{U}Cancel@{UU} ».

@EndNode

@Node MP3GenreList "GUI / MP3 genre list"

@{_Section "MP3 genre list"}

  This list gadget allows you to view all the TAG ID3 possible genres.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU} If you alter the contents of this gadget and press RETURN,  then  a
  requester  will prompt you to write the TAG ID3 in case you press « @{U}Okay@{UU} »
  or « @{U}Cancel@{UU} ».

@EndNode


@Node MP3GenrePopup "GUI / MP3 genre popup"

@{_Section "MP3 genre popup"}

  This popup gadget allows you to display the list of TAG ID3 genres.

@EndNode

@Node ADOSComment "GUI / AmigaDOS comment"

@{_Section "AmigaDOS comment"}

  This string gadget allows you to view/change the @{u}AmigaDOS@{uu} comment. You can
  press  the  hotkey  "Control  +  p"  inside the string gadget, in order to
  display the @{" Popup ListView " link MP3ADOSComList}.

  Holding the mouse some time over the bar above the string gadget  displays
  a bubble help indicating the shorcut to access this gadget.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU} If you alter the contents of this gadget and press @{i}RETURN @{ui}, then an
  @{u}AmigaDOS@{uu} comment will be written to the file. A requester  will  popup  in
  case of a problem.
@EndNode

@Node MP3ADOSComList "GUI / AmigaDOS comment Popup ListView"

@{_Section "AmigaDOS comment Popup ListView"}

  This ListView allows you to insert some TAG ID3  fields  in  the  @{u}AmigaDOS@{uu}
  comment  string  gadget.  The  list  only  contains  the available TAG ID3
  fields. Press @{i}RETURN @{ui}to insert an item and @{i}ESC @{ui}to leave the  list  without
  changing the @{u}AmigaDOS@{uu} comment string.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU} In order to SET the @{u}AmigaDOS@{uu} comment to the MPEG Audio file, you'll
  have to press @{i}RETURN @{ui}in the @{u}AmigaDOS@{uu} comment string gadget. This list only
  inserts a chosen TAG ID3 field in the string, nothing more.
@EndNode



@Node StatusText "GUI / Status text"

@{_Section "Status text"}

  This text gadget allows you to view the status of the  program.  It'll  be
  filled  up when you'll perform actions such as reading, writing and wiping
  the TAG ID3. It'll warn you  if  @{b}AmTAGID3@{ub}  isn't  able  to  calculate  the
  duration of the MPEG Audio file.

@EndNode

@Node Okay "GUI / Okay"

@{_Section "Okay"}

  This button gadget simply quits AmTAGID3.

  @{b}@{u}Note :@{ub}@{uu} If you have altered the contents  of  @{u}Title@{uu},  @{u}Artist@{uu},  @{u}Album@{uu},  @{u}Year@{uu}
  @{u}Genre@{uu} or @{u}Comment@{uu}, then a requester will ask you if you want to  write  the
  TAG ID3 before quitting.

@EndNode

@Node Write "GUI / Write"

@{_Section "Write"}

  This button gadget writes TAG ID3 to the MPEG Audio file.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU} If any problem occurs, a requester will popup.

@EndNode

@Node Wipe "GUI / Wipe"

@{_Section "Wipe"}

  This button gadget wipes the TAG  ID3  out  of  the  MPEG  Audio  file.  A
  requester will ask you for confirmation first.

  @{B}@{U}Note :@{UB}@{UU} If any problem occurs, a requester will popup.

@EndNode


@Node Cancel "GUI / Cancel"

@{_Section "Cancel"}

  This button gadget simply quits @{b}AmTAGID3@{ub}  but  generating  an  error  code
  level  of  @{u}40@{uu}.  This big level is bigger than RETURN_FAIL (which is 20) to
  ensure that the command will  @{u}STOP@{uu}  the  current  script  (if  any).  This
  behaviour  is  very  useful  on scripts. ie: If you're using a filemanager
  (like @{b}DOpus@{ub} or any other), select several files to process  with  @{b}AmTAGID3@{ub}
  and  for  some  reason  want  to  stop, then pressing « @{u}Cancel@{uu} » will STOP
  the script (or you have at the top of the script  a  @{u}FailAt@{uu}  command  with
  more than 40 as fail level !!!)


  @{b}@{u}Note :@{ub}@{uu} If you have altered the contents  of  @{u}Title@{uu},  @{u}Artist@{uu},  @{u}Album@{uu},  @{u}Year@{uu}
  @{u}Genre@{uu} or @{u}Comment@{uu}, then a requester will ask you if you want to  write  the
  TAG ID3 before quitting.

@EndNode

@Node Important "Important things to know"

@{_Section "Important things to know"}

  This section points out some problems  in  order  to  let  you  know  some
  important  things.  It can also serve as answers to some of your questions
  about my decisions on the features of this program.

  @{" Genres problem           " link GenresProblem}
  @{" Track number restriction " link TAGID3}

@EndNode

@Node History "AmTAGID3 / History"

@{_Section "History"}

  @{FG Highlight}Versions 1.0, 1.1, 1.2, 1.3@{FG Text}
    - Internal

  @{FG Highlight}Version 1.4@{FG Text}
    - First public release, waiting the flames :)

  @{FG Highlight}Version 1.5@{FG Text}
    - Fixed cosmetic bug with time display. "1:02" would be displayed "1:2"
    - Added more safety checks for MPEG Audio files. Should be a lot harder
      to fool now :)
    - Now using the @{" BetterString.mcc " link betterstring} from @{" Allan Odgaard " link credits}.
    - Added a @{" Popup ListView " link ADOSComList} which contains some of the TAG  ID3  fields
      to insert in the AmigaDOS Comment string gadgetstring gadget.
    - Fixed some cosmetic bugs on this guide :-P
    - Few internal minor changes/fixes.

  @{FG Highlight}Version 1.6@{FG Text}
    - Gosh! Forgot to talk about the shorcut to access the AmigaDOS
      @{" comment " link ADOSComment} string gadget...
    - Added lots of new genres (Picked them up from the most complete list
      at the moment : @{b}WinAmp@{ub} for @{b}Win95@{ub}/@{b}NT@{ub}). Now 141 genres available.
      @{u}@{b}WARNING@{uu}@{ub} : This change introduces a small problem! See @{" here " link GenresProblem} please!
    - Now the list of genres is alphabetically sorted.
      Suggested by @{u}Tomasz 'Domel' Kepa@{uu}

  @{FG Highlight}Version 1.7@{FG Text}
    - Now the field @{u}Year@{uu} is activated after pressing @{i}RETURN @{ui}in @{u}Artist@{uu} instead
      of activating @{u}Comment@{uu}. I thought nobody used this field, I was wrong :)
      Suggested by @{u}Teemu Kärkkäinen@{uu}
    - Added some new infos in section @{" Usage " link Usage} of the guide
    - Minor changes to the guide
    - The help node of the AmigaDOS comment @{" popup listview " link MP3ADOSComList} was wrong. Fixed.
    - The AmigaDOS comment @{" popup listview " link MP3ADOSComList} now auto adjustes its height.
    - If there is no entry in the AmigaDOS comment @{" popup listview " link MP3ADOSComList}, then it
      is disabled.
    - Added new command line option keyword @{" GL=GENRELINES/K/N " link GENRELINES}
      Suggested by @{u}Tomasz 'Domel' Kepa@{uu} & @{u}Jerôme 'Ours' Chesnot@{uu}
    - Added more @{" genres " link TheGenres} (now @{u}144@{uu} genres available)
    - Added new command line option switch @{" RS=REMSPACES/S " link REMSPACES}
    - Added support to @{b}MP3Encode@{ub}.
      Thanks to @{u}Tomasz 'Domel' Kepa@{uu} & @{u}Bruce Heller@{uu} for helping me :)
    - Made the program a bit less drastic in order to accept strange
      MPEG Audio specs. You should experience less error messages, saying
      that your file isn't a valid MPEG Audio file, than before :-)

  @{FG Highlight}Version 1.7a@{FG Text} - BUG FIX release
    - There are 145 genres. I said 144 previously :(
    - Removed a really stupid bug that made AmTAGID3 enter an endless loop
      and eat all your CPU time. Sorry folks, this can happen ;-)

  @{FG Highlight}Version 2.0@{FG Text} - MAJOR release
    - Now supports every incarnation of @{" MPEG Audio " link MPEGAUDIO} files
      Thanks to Didier 'Kakace' Levet for giving me the specs :)
    - Added support for @{" TrackNumber " link TrackNumber} field, part of @{"TAG ID3" link TAGID3} definition V1.1
    - Added new command line option switch @{" TN=TRACKNUMBER/S " link TrackNumber}
    - Added new command line option switch @{" NOGUI/S " link NOGUI}
    - Added new command line option switch @{" NI=NOINFO/S " link NOINFO}
    - Added new command line option switch @{" NT=NOTAGS/S " link NOTAGS}
    - Added new command line option switch @{" LI=LINEINFO/S " link LINEINFO}
    - Added new command line option switch @{" AC=AMIGACOMMENT/S " link AMIGACOMMENT}
    - Fixed a bug with setting the Genre ID for genre "Unset"
    - Fully localised now :-)

@EndNode

